&lt;p data-start="241" data-end="400"&gt;&lt;span class="large-para"&gt;&lt;img class="blog-img" src="https://blog-img.speedcurve.com/img/554/vitals-overview-1.png?auto=format,compress&amp;amp;fit=max&amp;amp;w=2000" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="402" data-end="484"&gt;When it comes to improving web performance, the journey usually looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;ol&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="488" data-end="526"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="488" data-end="500"&gt;Identify&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;where the problems are&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="488" data-end="526"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="530" data-end="542"&gt;Diagnose&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;why they&amp;rsquo;re happening&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="571" data-end="592"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="571" data-end="578"&gt;Fix&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the issues&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="596" data-end="633"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="596" data-end="608"&gt;Validate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;that the fixes worked&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;/ol&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="635" data-end="783"&gt;Our new Vitals Overview dashboard is designed to make that critical&amp;nbsp;&lt;em data-start="696" data-end="708"&gt;first step&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;mdash; identifying performance issues &amp;mdash; faster, clearer, and more actionable.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class="blog-img" src="https://blog-img.speedcurve.com/img/554/heatmap-location.png?auto=format,compress&amp;amp;fit=max&amp;amp;w=2000" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;h2 data-start="790" data-end="839"&gt;What are Web Vitals and why do they matter?&lt;/h2&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="840" data-end="1119"&gt;Web Vitals are a focused set of metrics that shine a light on the most important parts of the user experience. While SpeedCurve tracks a wide range of performance data, Vitals give you a quick, high-level view of where your site delights users&amp;hellip; or where it&amp;rsquo;s letting them down.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="1121" data-end="1176"&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s a quick snapshot of what each Vital tells you:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1179" data-end="1248"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1179" data-end="1211"&gt;Backend (Time to First Byte)&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; How quickly your server responds&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1251" data-end="1324"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1251" data-end="1277"&gt;First Contentful Paint&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; How fast something first appears on screen&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1327" data-end="1391"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1327" data-end="1355"&gt;Largest Contentful Paint&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; How fast the main visual content loads&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1394" data-end="1501"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1394" data-end="1466"&gt;Interaction to Next Paint (RUM) / JS Total Blocking Time (Synthetic)&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; How responsive your site feels&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1504" data-end="1574"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1504" data-end="1542"&gt;Total Blocking Duration (RUM only)&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; How busy the main thread is&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1577" data-end="1655"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1577" data-end="1604"&gt;Cumulative Layout Shift&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; How visually stable the page looks as it loads&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;/ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="1657" data-end="1741"&gt;Want to dig deeper? Check out our &lt;a class="decorated-link" href="#" rel="noopener" data-start="1691" data-end="1717"&gt;Web Performance Guide&lt;/a&gt; for a full breakdown.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;h2 data-start="1748" data-end="1787"&gt;A dashboard designed to guide you&lt;/h2&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="1788" data-end="1892"&gt;The Vitals Overview dashboard gives you a clear, color-coded snapshot of your performance at a glance:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1895" data-end="1913"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1895" data-end="1904"&gt;Green&lt;/strong&gt; = good&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1916" data-end="1948"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1916" data-end="1926"&gt;Yellow&lt;/strong&gt; = needs improvement&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="1951" data-end="1982"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="1951" data-end="1958"&gt;Red&lt;/strong&gt; = poor (time to act!)&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;/ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="1984" data-end="2247"&gt;At the very top, you&amp;rsquo;ll see your &lt;strong data-start="2017" data-end="2066"&gt;75th percentile performance across each vital&lt;/strong&gt;. When using real user monitoring (RUM) you'll also see a distribution of how many of&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;your actual users&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;are in each threshold when&amp;nbsp;experiencing your site.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="1984" data-end="2247"&gt;The goal: move as many users as possible into the green.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="1984" data-end="2247"&gt;&lt;img class="blog-img" src="https://blog-img.speedcurve.com/img/554/overview.png?auto=format,compress&amp;amp;fit=max&amp;amp;w=2000" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;h2 data-start="2254" data-end="2292"&gt;Spot issues faster with heatmaps&lt;/h2&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="2293" data-end="2380"&gt;Below the overview, heatmaps break down your performance across different dimensions:&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="2383" data-end="2489"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="2383" data-end="2394"&gt;By page&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Quickly spot the pages that are dragging performance down (ranked by traffic when using RUM)&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="2492" data-end="2563"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="2492" data-end="2510"&gt;By device type&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Uncover layout or responsive design bottlenecks&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="2566" data-end="2620"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="2566" data-end="2580"&gt;By browser&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Zero in on browser-specific issues&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;li data-start="2623" data-end="2689"&gt;&lt;strong data-start="2623" data-end="2638"&gt;By location&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Understand geographic performance differences&lt;/li&gt;&#13;
&lt;/ul&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="2691" data-end="2863"&gt;Each heatmap makes it easy to spot trouble areas. Just click into any yellow or red cell to drill deeper into diagnostics and start uncovering the &amp;ldquo;why&amp;rdquo; behind the issue.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="2691" data-end="2863"&gt;&lt;img class="blog-img" src="https://blog-img.speedcurve.com/img/554/heatmap-page-label.png?auto=format,compress&amp;amp;fit=max&amp;amp;w=2000" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;h2 data-start="2870" data-end="2904"&gt;Smarter insights, less noise&lt;/h2&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="2905" data-end="3139"&gt;To make sure you&amp;rsquo;re not chasing false signals, we&amp;rsquo;ve also added a new &lt;strong data-start="2975" data-end="3002"&gt;low-sample data warning&lt;/strong&gt; for RUM. This flags when data might be misleading because of a small sample size &amp;mdash; helping you focus on real issues, not red herrings.&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
&lt;p data-start="2905" data-end="3139"&gt;&lt;img class="blog-img" src="https://blog-img.speedcurve.com/img/554/low-data.png?auto=format,compress&amp;amp;fit=max&amp;amp;w=2000" alt="" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#13;
